    "Our system's exact geometry and material composition is unknown, and there is strong modal overlap (see Methods).",
    "However, it is easy to measure the transfer function (i.e., the 4 × 4 scattering matrix S defined through the antennas, or a subset thereof) for a few known random metasurface configurations.",
    "Is that enough to calibrate a model that accurately predicts the transfer function for any of the 2 68 possible metasurface configurations?",
    "Our system contains N = N A + N S wireless entities of primary interest (N A antennas to input/output waves, N S meta-atoms to control the system transfer function) that are naturally discrete.",
    "We model each entity as a dipole characterized by its polarizability (α A for the nominally identical antennas; α 0 or α 1 for the nominally identical 1-bit programmable meta-atoms, depending on their configuration)."
